[SN]TITLE[SN]
World Short Course Championships: Andrew Willis wins silver for Britain

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Andrew Willis won Great Britain's second medal of the World Short Course Championships in Windsor, Canada with silver in the 200m breaststroke.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Find out how to get into swimming with our special guide.
Willis, 26, set a personal best time of two minutes 02.71 seconds but was beaten to gold by Germany's Marco Koch.
Georgia Davies claimed Britain's first medal on Wednesday with bronze in the 100m backstroke.
Hannah Miley narrowly missed out on a medal when she finished fourth in the 400m individual medley.
The World Short Course Championships take place in a 25-metre pool, rather than the Olympic-size 50- metre pool.
